They accept Advanced Placement and life experience credit towards completion of a degree. Programs offered at Hampton University include bachelor's, master's and doctoral degrees in over 33 areas of study and 90 specializations. The school has been accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools, Commission on Colleges and has specialized accreditation from the Accreditation Council for Pharmacy Education.
